{pstd}{bf:maptile {hline 2} Geography: statehex}{p_end}


{marker description}{...}
{title:Description}

{pstd}{bf:statehex} generates a tile map with U.S. states depicted as hexagons.{p_end}

{pstd}Each state hexagon is labeled using 2-letter state abbreviations by default. The options {opth labelhex(varname)} or {opt nolabel} can apply different labels or remove the labels.{p_end}


{marker geographic-id-variables}{...}
{title:Geographic ID variables}

{synoptset 13 tabbed}{...}
{synopt:{bf:state}}2-letter state abbreviations{p_end}
{synopt:{bf:statefips}}2-digit state FIPS codes{p_end}
{synopt:{bf:statename}}unabbreviated state names{p_end}


{marker geography-specific-options}{...}
{title:Geography-Specific Options}

{synoptset tabbed}{...}
{synopt:{opth geoid(varname)}}specifies the geographic ID variable to use; default is {bf:geoid(state)}{p_end}
{synopt:{opth labelhex(varname)}}specifies a variable to label the state hexagons; default is 2-letter state abbreviations{p_end}
{synopt:{bf:nolabel}}removes the labels from the hexagons{p_end}


